{"type": "article", "id": 33019, "title": "美国最重要的图书奖之一出了决选名单，来看这 20 本好书", "description": "最终奖项结果将在 11 月 16 日于纽约宣布。", "date": "2016-10-08T10:30:29Z", "super_tag": "", "tags": [{"id": 26438, "name": "普利策奖"}, {"id": 33674, "name": "美国国家图书奖"}], "category": 5, "author": 589058, "comment_count": 4, "praise_count": 446, "image": "img/article/article_show/20161008154636UdQJco0ADvxWnrqL.jpg", "contents": "<p><a href=\"http://www.npr.org/sections/thetwo-way/2016/10/06/496760469/these-are-the-2016-national-book-award-finalists\" rel=\"nofollow\">本周</a>， 2016 年美国国家图书奖决选名单揭晓，包括小说、非小说、诗歌和青少文学 4 个门类共 20 本书入围此次名单。</p><p><a href=\"http://blogs.wsj.com/speakeasy/2016/10/06/national-book-award-finalists-are-announced/\" rel=\"nofollow\">据《华尔街日报》报道</a>，本届美国国家图书奖共有 1464 部作品参与评选。在最终入围的 20 部作品中，只有杰奎琳·伍德森（Jacqueline Woodson）和凯特·迪卡米洛（Kate DiCamillo）两位作者曾经获得过该奖项的青少文学奖，其余都是新人。不过此次杰奎琳·伍德森入围美国国家图书奖的作品《另一个布鲁克林》（<em><em>Another Brooklyn）</em></em>是她首部成人文学作品。</p><p><a href=\"https://www.theguardian.com/books/2016/oct/06/colson-whitehead-national-book-awards-fiction-shortlist\" rel=\"nofollow\">据《卫报》报道</a>，在小说领域，科尔森·怀特海德(Colson Whitehead)的作品《地下铁路》（<i>The Underground Railroad</i>）较有希望获得这一奖项。今年八月，《地下铁路》一书入选了有阅读届风向标之称的“奥普拉读书俱乐部”新书推荐。该书讲述的是在美国佐治亚州棉花种植园里，一个年轻奴隶努力争取自由的故事。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161008160630n9YOXzalHZt0eTDK.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666319\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\">来自：<a href=\"http://blogs.wsj.com/speakeasy/2016/10/06/national-book-award-finalists-are-announced/\" rel=\"nofollow\">wsj</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>而在非小说领域， Heather Ann Thompson 关于 1971 年美国阿提卡（Attica）监狱暴动的作品<i> Blood in the Water </i>入围此次美国国家图书奖。除此之外，入围的还有普利策奖得主 Viet Thanh Nguyen 反映越南战争的作品 <i>Nothing Ever Dies</i> 。</p><p><a href=\"http://www.nytimes.com/2016/10/07/books/national-book-awards-finalists-include-colson-whitehead-and-viet-thanh-nguyen.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">据《纽约时报》报道</a>，今年美国国家图书奖的终身成就奖将颁给罗伯特·A·卡洛（Robert A. Caro）。他是美国前总统林顿·约翰逊的传记作家，其作品《成为官僚》还获得过普利策奖和帕克曼奖。而 2016 年美国国家图书奖的最终奖项结果将在 11 月 16 日于纽约宣布。</p><p>美国国家图书奖是由美国出版商协会、美国书商协会和图书制造商协会于 1950 年 3 月 16 日联合设立的图书奖项。每年颁发一次，获奖者可获得 10000 美金和一枚铜质雕塑，入围者也可每人获得 1000 美元和一枚奖章。</p><p>它与普利策小说奖被视为美国最重要的两个文学奖项。此前包括威廉·福克纳、索尔·贝娄、菲利普·罗斯、苏珊·桑塔格、欧逸文和哈金等都获得过该奖项。</p><h3><b><a href=\"http://www.nationalbook.org/nba2016.html#.V_ibPrh95v2\" rel=\"nofollow\">完整入围名单如下（非常抱歉，这里就不翻译了）：</a></b></h3><h3>小说类：</h3><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161008160437Tn74pKMsrm8xJ62L.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.360039\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\">来自：<a href=\"http://www.nationalbook.org/nba2016.html#.V_ibPrh95v2\" rel=\"nofollow\">nationalbook</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>Chris Bachelder , &nbsp;<b><i><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Throwback-Special-Novel-Chris-Bachelder/dp/0393249468/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1475912894&amp;sr=8-1&amp;keywords=The+Throwback+Special\" rel=\"nofollow\">The Throwback Special</a>&nbsp;</i></b><br></p><p>Paulette Jiles , <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/News-World-Novel-Paulette-Jiles/dp/0062409204/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1475912926&amp;sr=8-1&amp;keywords=News+of+the+World\" rel=\"nofollow\">&nbsp;<b><i>News of the World</i></b></a><b></b><br></p><p>Karan Mahajan , &nbsp;<b><i><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Association-Small-Bombs-Novel/dp/0525429638/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1475912952&amp;sr=8-1&amp;keywords=The+Association+of+Small+Bombs\" rel=\"nofollow\">The Association of Small Bombs</a></i></b><br></p><p>Colson Whitehead , &nbsp;<i><b><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Underground-Railroad-Oprahs-Book-Club/dp/0385542364/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1475910257&amp;sr=8-1&amp;keywords=The+Underground+Railroad\" rel=\"nofollow\">The Underground Railroad</a>&nbsp;</b></i><br></p><p>Jacqueline Woodson ,&nbsp;<b><i><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Another-Brooklyn-Novel-Jacqueline-Woodson/dp/0062359983/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1475912982&amp;sr=8-1&amp;keywords=Another+Brooklyn\" rel=\"nofollow\">Another Brooklyn</a>&nbsp;</i></b><br></p><h3>非小说类：</h3><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161008160515rsuN2ZDOlX4xeHhm.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.343604\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\">来自：\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.nationalbook.org/nba2016.html#.V_ibPrh95v2\" rel=\"nofollow\">nationalbook</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>Arlie Russell Hochschild, <i><b><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Strangers-Their-Own-Land-Mourning/dp/1620972255/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1475913012&amp;sr=8-1&amp;keywords=Strangers+in+Their+Own+Land%3A+Anger+and+Mourning+on+the+American+Right\" rel=\"nofollow\">Strangers in Their Own Land: Anger and Mourning on the American Right</a>&nbsp;</b></i><br></p><p>Ibram X. Kendi, <i><b><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Stamped-Beginning-Definitive-History-America/dp/1568584636/ref=sr_1_1?s=books&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1475913041&amp;sr=1-1&amp;keywords=Stamped+from+the+Beginning%3A+The+Definitive+History+of+Racist+Ideas+in+America\" rel=\"nofollow\">Stamped from the Beginning: The Definitive History of Racist Ideas in America</a>&nbsp;</b></i><br></p><p>Viet Thanh Nguyen, &nbsp;<b><i><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Nothing-Ever-Dies-Vietnam-Memory/dp/067466034X/ref=sr_1_1?s=books&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1475913075&amp;sr=1-1&amp;keywords=Nothing+Ever+Dies%3A+Vietnam+and+the+Memory+of+War\" rel=\"nofollow\">Nothing Ever Dies: Vietnam and the Memory of War</a>&nbsp;</i></b><br></p><p>Andrés Reséndez , &nbsp;<i><b><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Other-Slavery-Uncovered-Enslavement-America/dp/0547640986/ref=sr_1_1?s=books&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1475913108&amp;sr=1-1&amp;keywords=The+Other+Slavery%3A+The+Uncovered+Story+of+Indian+Enslavement+in+America\" rel=\"nofollow\">The Other Slavery: The Uncovered Story of Indian Enslavement in America</a>&nbsp;</b></i><br></p><p>Heather Ann Thompson , &nbsp;<b><i><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Blood-Water-Attica-Prison-Uprising/dp/0375423222/ref=sr_1_1?s=books&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1475913137&amp;sr=1-1&amp;keywords=Blood+in+the+Water%3A+The+Attica+Prison+Uprising+of+1971+and+Its+Legacy\" rel=\"nofollow\">Blood in the Water: The Attica Prison Uprising of 1971 and Its Legacy</a>&nbsp;</i></b><br></p><h3>诗歌类：</h3><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161008160536Tsk0XQ7DcIrbRAV3.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.351887\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\">来自：\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.nationalbook.org/nba2016.html#.V_ibPrh95v2\" rel=\"nofollow\">nationalbook</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>Daniel Borzutzky , &nbsp;<b><i>The Performance of Becoming Human </i></b></p><p>Rita Dove , &nbsp;<b><i>Collected Poems 1974 - 2004 </i></b></p><p>Peter Gizzi , &nbsp;<b><i>Archeophonics </i></b></p><p>Jay Hopler , &nbsp;<b><i>The Abridged History of Rainfall </i></b></p><p>Solmaz Sharif ,<b> <i>Look </i></b></p><h3>青少文学类：</h3><div class=\"com-insert-images\">&nbsp;<figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201610081605487PeaBDpiJK4cjbt1.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.351711\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\">来自：\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.nationalbook.org/nba2016.html#.V_ibPrh95v2\" rel=\"nofollow\">nationalbook</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>Kate DiCamillo ,<b>&nbsp;<i> Raymie Nightingale </i></b></p><p class=\"\">John Lewis , &nbsp;Andrew Aydin &nbsp;&amp; &nbsp;Nate Powell &nbsp;(Artist) , &nbsp;<b><i>March: Book Three </i></b></p><p>Grace Lin , &nbsp;<b><i>When the Sea Turned to Silver</i></b> </p><p>Jason Reynolds , <i>&nbsp;<b>Ghost </b></i></p><p>Nicola Yoon , &nbsp;<b><i>The Sun Is Also a Star&nbsp;</i></b></p><p class=\"\">题图来自：<a href=\"http://www.nytimes.com/2016/10/07/books/national-book-awards-finalists-include-colson-whitehead-and-viet-thanh-nguyen.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">nytimes</a></p>"}